Class DoubleList

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cicirello.util.DoubleList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Copyable<DoubleList>
    public final class DoubleList
extends Object
implements Copyable<DoubleList>
    This class is an implementation of a partially-filled array of primitive double values.

        public DoubleList​(int initialCapacity)
        Initializes an empty DoubleList, with a specified initial capacity. This may be useful if you anticipate adding a large number of elements as it can help minimize the number of array reallocations.
        Parameters:
        initialCapacity - The initial capacity for the buffer array holding the contents.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if initialCapacity is less than 1.

        Throws:

      • trimToSize

        public void trimToSize()
        Reduces the capacity of the list to the current value of size(). However, if size() is 0, this method will trim the list capacity to 1. If you don't anticipate adding additional elements to the list, and if your application is memory constrained, then this method can save memory.
